title: Inauguration of Joe Biden
deleted: Either Biden (at 78) or Trump (at 74) taking the oath of office on January 20, 2021, would make one of them the oldest person ever to be sworn in as President, surpassing the record of [[Ronald Reagan|Reagan]] (at 73) who was sworn in for second term in [[Second inauguration of Ronald Reagan|1985]].
